The paper deals with satisfiability problems with a linear structure, which suggests that it may belong to the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem, which could place it in the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of linear orders and graphs suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the NP-hardness of recognizing 1-interval bigraphs, which could place it in the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
